## Overview

This document defines the standards for the Voice AI Operations Panel frontend. This is an internal ops/admin panel for monitoring and managing the Voice AI Runtime. It is built with Next.js 15 App Router, prioritizing server-side rendering, type safety, and operational efficiency.

## Technology Stack

### Core Technologies
- **Next.js 15**: App Router with React Server Components
- **TypeScript 5**: Strict mode, full type safety
- **React 19**: Server Components, Suspense, use() hook

### UI Framework
- **Tailwind CSS 4**: Utility-first CSS framework
- **shadcn/ui**: Accessible, composable component library (not installed as dependency — components are copied into the project)
- **Lucide Icons**: Icon library (used by shadcn/ui)

### State Management & Data Flow
- **React Server Components**: Default for data fetching
- **React Query (TanStack Query)**: Client-side async state for real-time data
- **nuqs**: Type-safe URL search params state management
- **Server Actions**: Form mutations and data writes

### Package Manager
- **pnpm**: Fast, disk-efficient package manager

### Development Tools
- **ESLint**: With Next.js and TypeScript rules
- **Prettier**: Code formatting (via eslint-plugin-prettier)
- **TypeScript**: Strict type checking

