## Coding Standards

### Naming Conventions

- **Components**: `PascalCase` (`CallDetail`, `MetricsDashboard`, `RoutingEditor`)
- **Variables/functions**: `camelCase` (`callId`, `handleSubmit`, `formatDuration`)
- **Constants**: `UPPER_SNAKE_CASE` (`API_BASE_URL`, `MAX_CALLS_PER_PAGE`)
- **Types/interfaces**: `PascalCase` (`CallSession`, `TurnData`, `RouteConfig`)
- **Files**: `kebab-case` for non-component files (`api-client.ts`, `use-calls.ts`)
- **Component files**: `kebab-case` matching the component (`call-detail.tsx`, `metrics-dashboard.tsx`)
- **CSS classes**: Tailwind utilities; custom classes in `kebab-case`
- **Hooks**: `camelCase` prefixed with `use` (`useCalls`, `useMetrics`)

### Language

All code, comments, commit messages, and documentation must be in **English**.

```typescript
// Good
const fetchCallHistory = async (limit: number): Promise<CallSession[]> => {
  // Fetch recent call sessions from the API
};

// Bad
const obtenerHistorialLlamadas = async (limite: number): Promise<CallSession[]> => {
  // Obtener sesiones de llamada recientes de la API
};
```

### TypeScript Usage

- **Strict mode**: Always enabled in `tsconfig.json`
- **No `any`**: Use `unknown` or specific types
- **Prefer `interface`** for object shapes, `type` for unions/intersections
- **Use `satisfies`** for type-safe object literals
- **Use `as const`** for literal types

```typescript
// Good: explicit types
interface CallSession {
  callId: string;
  status: "active" | "ended";
  startedAt: number;
  endedAt: number | null;
  turnCount: number;
}

// Good: satisfies for type checking without widening
const DEFAULT_FILTERS = {
  status: "all",
  limit: 50,
  sortBy: "startedAt",
} satisfies CallFilters;
```

### Import Order

Enforce consistent import ordering:

```typescript
// 1. React/Next.js
import { Suspense } from "react";
import Link from "next/link";

// 2. Third-party libraries
import { useQuery } from "@tanstack/react-query";

// 3. Internal components
import { CallCard } from "@/components/calls/call-card";

// 4. Internal utilities
import { cn, formatDuration } from "@/lib/utils";

// 5. Types
import type { CallSession } from "@/lib/types";
```

## Component Conventions

### Server Components (Default)

All components are Server Components by default. Only add `"use client"` when necessary (event handlers, hooks, browser APIs).

```typescript
// app/calls/page.tsx — Server Component (default)
import { CallList } from "@/components/calls/call-list";
import { getCalls } from "@/lib/api";

export default async function CallsPage() {
  const calls = await getCalls({ limit: 50 });

  return (
    <div className="container mx-auto py-6">
      <h1 className="text-2xl font-bold mb-4">Call History</h1>
      <CallList calls={calls} />
    </div>
  );
}
```

### Client Components

Only use `"use client"` for interactive components:

```typescript
"use client";

import { useState } from "react";
import { Button } from "@/components/ui/button";

interface CallFilterProps {
  onFilter: (filters: CallFilters) => void;
}

export function CallFilter({ onFilter }: CallFilterProps) {
  const [status, setStatus] = useState<string>("all");
  // ...
}
```

### Component Props

- Define props with `interface` at the top of the file
- Use destructuring in function signature
- Avoid prop drilling — use composition or context

```typescript
interface MetricsCardProps {
  title: string;
  value: number;
  unit: string;
  trend?: "up" | "down" | "stable";
}

export function MetricsCard({ title, value, unit, trend }: MetricsCardProps) {
  return (
    <div className="rounded-lg border p-4">
      <p className="text-sm text-muted-foreground">{title}</p>
      <p className="text-2xl font-bold">
        {value} <span className="text-sm">{unit}</span>
      </p>
    </div>
  );
}
```

### Composition Pattern

Prefer composition over complex props:

```typescript
// Good: composition
<Card>
  <CardHeader>
    <CardTitle>Call Details</CardTitle>
  </CardHeader>
  <CardContent>
    <CallTimeline turns={turns} />
  </CardContent>
</Card>

// Avoid: prop overload
<Card title="Call Details" content={<CallTimeline turns={turns} />} />
```

## State Management & Data Flow

### Data Fetching Strategy

| Data Type | Strategy | Example |
|-----------|----------|---------|
| Static/rarely changes | Server Component + `fetch` | Call history page |
| Real-time/polling | React Query + client component | Live metrics dashboard |
| URL state (filters, pagination) | `nuqs` search params | Call list filters |
| Form mutations | Server Actions | Settings updates |
| Ephemeral UI state | `useState` | Modal open/close |

### API Client

Centralize all API calls in `lib/api.ts`:

```typescript
const API_BASE = process.env.NEXT_PUBLIC_API_URL ?? "http://localhost:8000";

async function apiFetch<T>(path: string, init?: RequestInit): Promise<T> {
  const res = await fetch(`${API_BASE}${path}`, {
    ...init,
    headers: {
      "Content-Type": "application/json",
      ...init?.headers,
    },
  });

  if (!res.ok) {
    throw new ApiError(res.status, await res.text());
  }

  return res.json() as Promise<T>;
}

export const api = {
  calls: {
    list: (params?: CallFilters) => apiFetch<CallSession[]>(`/api/v1/calls`, { next: { revalidate: 10 } }),
    get: (callId: string) => apiFetch<CallDetail>(`/api/v1/calls/${callId}`),
  },
  metrics: {
    summary: () => apiFetch<MetricsSummary>(`/api/v1/metrics/summary`),
  },
};
```

### React Query (Client-Side Real-Time)

```typescript
"use client";

import { useQuery } from "@tanstack/react-query";
import { api } from "@/lib/api";

export function useActiveCalls() {
  return useQuery({
    queryKey: ["calls", "active"],
    queryFn: () => api.calls.list({ status: "active" }),
    refetchInterval: 5_000, // Poll every 5s for live data
  });
}
```

### Server Actions

```typescript
"use server";

import { revalidatePath } from "next/cache";

export async function updateThresholds(formData: FormData) {
  const thresholds = Object.fromEntries(formData);
  await api.routing.updateThresholds(thresholds);
  revalidatePath("/routing");
}
```

## UI/UX Standards

### shadcn/ui Usage

- Install components via CLI: `pnpm dlx shadcn@latest add button card table`
- Components live in `components/ui/`
- Customize via Tailwind — never modify shadcn source directly
- Use the `cn()` utility for conditional classes

```typescript
import { cn } from "@/lib/utils";

<div className={cn(
  "rounded-lg border p-4",
  isActive && "border-green-500 bg-green-50",
  isError && "border-red-500 bg-red-50",
)}>
```

### Layout

- Use the App Router layout system (`layout.tsx`)
- Sidebar navigation for main sections
- Responsive design with Tailwind breakpoints
- Dark mode support via shadcn/ui theme

### Accessibility

- All interactive elements must be keyboard accessible (shadcn/ui handles this)
- Use semantic HTML elements
- Include `aria-label` for icon-only buttons
- Provide alt text for images

### Loading States

Use React Suspense with loading UI:

```typescript
// app/calls/loading.tsx
import { Skeleton } from "@/components/ui/skeleton";

export default function Loading() {
  return (
    <div className="space-y-4">
      <Skeleton className="h-8 w-48" />
      <Skeleton className="h-64 w-full" />
    </div>
  );
}
```

### Error Handling

Use Next.js error boundaries:

```typescript
// app/calls/error.tsx
"use client";

export default function Error({ error, reset }: { error: Error; reset: () => void }) {
  return (
    <div className="flex flex-col items-center gap-4 py-12">
      <p className="text-destructive">Failed to load calls: {error.message}</p>
      <Button onClick={reset}>Retry</Button>
    </div>
  );
}
```

## Testing Standards

### Test Organization

```
frontend/
+-- __tests__/
|   +-- components/
|   |   +-- call-detail.test.tsx
|   +-- lib/
|   |   +-- api.test.ts
|   +-- e2e/
|       +-- calls.spec.ts
```

### Component Testing

Use React Testing Library with Vitest:

```typescript
import { render, screen } from "@testing-library/react";
import { MetricsCard } from "@/components/metrics/metrics-card";

describe("MetricsCard", () => {
  it("renders title and value", () => {
    render(<MetricsCard title="Avg Latency" value={42} unit="ms" />);

    expect(screen.getByText("Avg Latency")).toBeInTheDocument();
    expect(screen.getByText("42")).toBeInTheDocument();
  });
});
```

### E2E Testing

Use Playwright for end-to-end tests:

```typescript
import { test, expect } from "@playwright/test";

test("call history page loads and displays calls", async ({ page }) => {
  await page.goto("/calls");
  await expect(page.getByRole("heading", { name: "Call History" })).toBeVisible();
  await expect(page.getByRole("table")).toBeVisible();
});
```

### Coverage

- **Component tests**: Cover all interactive components
- **API client tests**: Cover error handling and edge cases
- **E2E tests**: Cover critical user flows (view calls, check metrics, edit routing)

